A student who has met the objectives of the course will be able to:
• Understand, explain and apply basic coordination
paradigms;
• Model a distributed application based on the covered
coordination paradigms;
• Identify and solve typical concurrency and communication
issues;
• Implement a simple distributed application based on the covered
coordination paradigms;
• Deploy a simple distributed application on different
networks;
• Organize, plan, and carry out collaborative software
development in a small group;
• Describe and explain the design and implementation of a simple
distributed application;
